---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="PX Org Strategy · Mollie Cox"
  description="Evolving a product design function into a strategic Product Experience organization spanning design, content, documentation, research, education, community, and AI."
>
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <!-- HERO -->
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <section class="case-hero-dark">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20 md:py-32 relative z-10">
      <a
        href="/#work"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cream/60 hover:text-orange transition-colors mb-16"
      >
        ← All work
      </a>

      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-6">Branch · 2025 to 2026</p>

      <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-cream leading-[0.95] tracking-tight max-w-[22ch]">
        From design function to product experience organization<span class="brand-period">.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-cream/80 leading-relaxed max-w-[48ch]">
        Evolving a design-centered team into a multi-disciplinary product organization
        spanning design, content, documentation, research, product education, customer
        community, and AI-enabled experience quality. Six pillars. One North Star. A
        measurable maturity model.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-20 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 pt-10 border-t border-cream/15 relative z-10">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Role</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Sr. Director, Product Experience</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Duration</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Multi-quarter</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Team</p>
          <p class="text-cream">~15-person org scope</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Outcome</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Operating model adopted</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- North Star -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop border-b border-ink/10 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-8">The North Star</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink leading-[1.0] tracking-tight max-w-[24ch]" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5.5vw, 5rem);">
        Make the product easier to understand, easier to adopt, <span class="text-orange italic">and harder to leave.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-12 text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
        Customer-centric. Business-relevant. Not design-centric. This framing was the
        unlock. It connects directly to usability, adoption, retention, customer
        confidence, product clarity, education, trust, and experience quality.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The problem -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The problem</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight">
          Growing scope, no shared operating model.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 max-w-reading">
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The Product Experience function already extended beyond traditional product
          design. The team owned product design, UX research, product content,
          technical documentation, design systems, customer programs, in-product
          education, product quality, and emerging AI experience patterns.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-6">
          But without a clear strategy, that breadth looked like a collection of
          responsibilities rather than a coherent function. The company was entering a
          major product transformation across modernization, AI, analytics, and
          customer migration. Design could no longer operate as a downstream service
          function making screens after decisions were already made.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          PX needed to become a strategic product partner with a defined scope, a
          shared operating model, and measurable outcomes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- THE SIX PILLARS - visual grid -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream-warm/40 border-y border-ink/10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The framework</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[24ch] mb-16">
        Six pillars under one North Star.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 md:gap-6">

        <!-- 01 Experience Quality -->
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="28" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
              <path d="M28 40 L 36 48 L 54 30" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar 01</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Experience Quality.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            UX quality, interaction patterns, design review, usability, accessibility,
            visual consistency, cross-product coherence. How PX protects the customer
            from organizational fragmentation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 02 Platform & Delivery -->
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <rect x="14" y="14" width="20" height="20" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <rect x="46" y="14" width="20" height="20" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <rect x="14" y="46" width="20" height="20" fill="#02101D"/>
              <rect x="46" y="46" width="20" height="20" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="34" y1="24" x2="46" y2="24" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="24" y1="34" x2="24" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="56" y1="34" x2="56" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar 02</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Experience Platform & Delivery.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Design system, component governance, design-engineering partnership, UI
            infrastructure, delivery standards. Where PX moves from craft to
            infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 03 Content & Clarity -->
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <rect x="12" y="14" width="56" height="52" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="26" x2="60" y2="26" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="34" x2="60" y2="34" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="42" x2="52" y2="42" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="50" x2="56" y2="50" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="58" x2="44" y2="58" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style="color: #9B40C4;">Pillar 03</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Content & Clarity.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Product content, UX writing, technical documentation, help content, in-product
            language. Customers cannot adopt what they cannot understand.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 04 Research & Insights -->
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="18" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
              <line x1="22" y1="24" x2="42" y2="24" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="22" y1="32" x2="42" y2="32" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="22" y1="40" x2="38" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="48" y1="48" x2="68" y2="68" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar 04</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Research & Insights.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            UX research, usability testing, VOC synthesis, customer visits, feedback
            loops into product strategy. PX helps the company make better product
            decisions by making customer signal easier to see and act on.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 05 Product Mastery & Community -->
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <circle cx="26" cy="32" r="10" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <circle cx="54" cy="32" r="10" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="52" r="10" fill="#02101D"/>
              <line x1="32" y1="36" x2="36" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="48" y1="36" x2="44" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="34" y1="34" x2="46" y2="34" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style="color: #9B40C4;">Pillar 05</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Product Mastery & Community.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Customer education, advisory programs, community-led learning, adoption
            support. Product mastery is part of product experience. It is how customers
            become confident, capable, and loyal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 06 AI & Intelligence -->
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <rect x="20" y="20" width="40" height="40" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
              <rect x="28" y="28" width="24" height="24" fill="#02101D"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="4" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="28" x2="14" y2="28" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="40" x2="14" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="52" x2="14" y2="52" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="60" y1="28" x2="66" y2="28" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="60" y1="40" x2="66" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="60" y1="52" x2="66" y2="52" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="28" y1="20" x2="28" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="40" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="52" y1="20" x2="52" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="28" y1="60" x2="28" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="40" y1="60" x2="40" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="52" y1="60" x2="52" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Pillar 06</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">AI & Intelligence.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            AI product patterns, AI-powered insights, product voice for AI, research and
            tooling acceleration. AI changes how customers understand, trust, and
            interact with the product.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The operating model shift -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-ink text-cream py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-8">The operating model shift</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16">
        <div class="max-w-reading">
          <p class="font-display text-3xl text-orange mb-6">Before</p>
          <p class="font-display text-2xl text-cream leading-tight mb-6">
            Design makes the product usable.
          </p>
          <p class="text-cream/70 leading-relaxed">
            Function defined by craft boundary. Design as downstream service. Screens
            after decisions.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-reading">
          <p class="font-display text-3xl text-orange mb-6">After</p>
          <p class="font-display text-2xl text-cream leading-tight mb-6">
            Product Experience makes the product understandable, adoptable, scalable, and trustworthy<span class="text-orange">.</span>
          </p>
          <p class="text-cream/70 leading-relaxed">
            Function defined by customer outcomes. PX as strategic product partner. The
            connective tissue between strategy, quality, and adoption.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Measurable maturity targets -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Maturity targets</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[26ch] mb-12">
      Measurable as a business function, not just visible as a craft.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft max-w-reading mb-12">
      The strategy included measurable maturity targets across each pillar so the
      function could be evaluated like any other strategic capability.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-4">
      {[
        { area: 'Design system adoption', target: '90%' },
        { area: 'UX quality score', target: '≥ 8.5' },
        { area: 'Design cycle reduction', target: '25%' },
        { area: 'Content consistency', target: '90%' },
        { area: 'Research velocity', target: '3×' },
        { area: 'Product mastery / internal certification', target: '90%' },
        { area: 'AI task automation', target: '40%' },
        { area: 'Post-launch adoption review cadence', target: '90 days' },
      ].map((row) => (
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between py-5 border-b border-ink/10">
          <p class="font-display text-lg text-ink">{row.area}</p>
          <p class="stat-num">{row.target}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-ink-muted font-mono max-w-reading">
      These are 2026 maturity targets, not realized outcomes. The strategy was designed to make Product Experience measurable as a business function.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- What made this executive (3-pillar) -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream-warm/40 border-y border-ink/10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">What made this executive</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-16">
        Defining a function, not leading work inside one.
      </h2>

      <div class="pillar-grid">

        <!-- Function design -->
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <rect x="12" y="14" width="56" height="52" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="26" x2="68" y2="26" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="40" y1="26" x2="40" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="46" x2="40" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="40" y1="46" x2="68" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
              <circle cx="26" cy="36" r="2" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
              <circle cx="26" cy="56" r="2" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
              <circle cx="54" cy="36" r="2" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
              <circle cx="54" cy="56" r="2" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-meta">
            <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Function design</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
              Architecting the role of PX itself.
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-body">
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Most design leadership work is leading projects inside an existing function.
              This was defining what the function does. Defining its scope, its
              outcomes, and its place in the broader product org.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Cross-functional integration -->
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <circle cx="26" cy="26" r="10" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <circle cx="54" cy="26" r="10" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="54" r="10" fill="#02101D"/>
              <line x1="33" y1="32" x2="36" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="47" y1="32" x2="44" y2="46" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="34" y1="26" x2="46" y2="26" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-meta">
            <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-3">Cross-functional integration</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
              Connecting disciplines into one system.
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-body">
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Design, content, research, documentation, education, community, and AI
              all under one strategic identity. The team got a shared language for
              priorities and tradeoffs.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-tagline">
            <p class="font-display text-2xl italic text-orange">"One system, six pillars."</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Measurement maturity -->
        <div class="pillar">
          <div class="pillar-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <line x1="14" y1="14" x2="14" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <line x1="14" y1="66" x2="66" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M22 58 L 34 44 L 44 50 L 60 24" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <circle cx="22" cy="58" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
              <circle cx="34" cy="44" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
              <circle cx="44" cy="50" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
              <circle cx="60" cy="24" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-meta">
            <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Measurement maturity</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
              Targets, not just intentions.
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-body">
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Every pillar had measurable targets. Design system adoption percentage. UX
              quality score. Research cadence. Content consistency. Internal product
              certification. AI task automation. PX could be evaluated like any
              strategic capability.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Meta-point -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop overflow-hidden border-b border-ink/10">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-28 md:py-36 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-8">The meta-point</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-ink leading-[0.95] tracking-tight mb-12" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);">
        Product Experience can't be defined by discipline boundaries.<br/>
        <span class="text-orange">It's defined by customer outcomes.</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Understanding. Adoption. Confidence. Loyalty. That gave the team a stronger
          strategic identity, and the company a clearer way to invest in product
          quality. The work that most differentiates a Sr. Director from a VP isn't
          choosing a process framework. It's defining the function itself.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
